To scale down the MySQL cluster, perform a normal upgrade and set the *slave.replicas* value to the desired number of nodes. For example, reduce the cluster to a single replica using the command below. Replace the  ROOT_PASSWORD placeholder with the MySQL *root* password.

~~~
$ helm upgrade bitnami/mysql \
  --set rootUser.password=ROOT_PASSWORD \
  --set slave.replicas=1 \
~~~
